                <note rend="inline" type="source">853.00 Revolution 1931/1: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">South</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-06T16:00:00+00:00"
                            >April 6, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. I am reliably informed Funchal, Madeira, in the hands of rebels. Have not
                    heard from Consul Huddleston. Two gunboats with troops leaving Lisbon today for
                    Madeira.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">South</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
